Package: stockflow
Title: Integrated Workflow for Length-Based Fish Stock Assessment
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person(given = "Kamarel",
           family = "Ba",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "bakamarel@gmail.com")
Description: An integrated, reproducible workflow for data-limited fish stock
    assessment based on length-frequency data. Provides robust wrappers around
    established scientific packages for data import and validation, growth
    estimation (ELEFAN via 'TropFishR'), natural and total mortality (including
    the empirical estimators of 'FSA' and 'TropFishR'), length-weight allometry,
    Length-Based Bayesian Biomass ('LBB'), Length-Based Spawning Potential Ratio
    ('LBSPR'), simulation of management measures, and automated reporting. The
    package never re-implements the underlying scientific algorithms; it composes
    the official implementations into a coherent, documented pipeline.
